race.comment: SALARY MAN (9) just missed two back before a disappointing performance at Belmont last start over 2100m. Back in trip slightly today, but he's well placed here on what he's done recently. Visors replace the blinkers today and he can end his winning drought in what looks a suitable event. HIGH PRECISION (8) comes through the same race at Belmont where she got a long way back and never fired a shot. Her form prior was solid, including a narrow defeat at this track and trip three back. Needs some luck from the draw, but has proven she's capable in a race like this. SIDE SHOW (3) jumps up in trip today following a poor performance at Belmont where the trainer said he didn't handle an uneven surface. The rise in trip looks suitable now however and he'll find this a much easier task. Can put his best foot forward. POINT OF LUCK (6) will appreciate this grade today and can bounce back. WARRALEA DIAMOND (4) won narrowly here two back and is not to be discounted.
